  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This program aims to improve the growth, anemia status, feeding, and health of children through a Nutrition Screening System (NSS) that facilitates the ongoing identification of malnourished children and those at risk, monitoring of growth and anemia status, treatment and follow-up care; equipping local staff to regularly screen children for growth and anemia and take necessary treatment actions such as providing iron supplements; and training key local staff as trainers for caregivers on culturally appropriate best practices in nutrition, feeding, sanitation and hygiene.</narrative>
  </description>
